    },
    "MissionGiver": "MicroTech",
    "Title": "RESOURCE DRIVE: LARGE CARGO THEFT",
    "TitleKey": "GoblinG_MicroTech_RecoverCargoFPS_L_Title",
    "Description": "Outlaws have been targeting the valuable resources we need to compete in the UEE initiative. Fortunately, implanted trackers in the cargo indicate that it\u2019s being held at <EM4>~mission(Location|Address)</EM4>. We just need someone to go and get it.\n\nThis situation is far from optimal, but I\u2019m hoping you\u2019ll be able to deal with the thieves and return the <EM4>~mission(ItemsToRecover) cargo boxes (all ~mission(MaxBoxSize) SCU or smaller)</EM4> to us. I\u2019ve done some quick calculations on the number of reported outlaws and would advise bringing <EM4>additional support</EM4> if possible.\n\nAfter you\u2019ve recovered the cargo, you can bring it to a freight elevator at: <EM4>~mission(Destination|Address|ListAll)</EM4>. Our logistics team can process it from there.\n\nObviously, the more you can recover the better, but we\u2019ll take whatever you can get.\n\nBest of luck with this one, you\u2019ll need it.\n\n\nAster Remmington\nContractor Liaison Officer\nmicroTech",
    "DescriptionKey": "GoblinG_MicroTech_RecoverCargoFPS_L_Desc",
    "DisplayDescription": "Outlaws have been targeting the valuable resources we need to compete in the UEE initiative. Fortunately, implanted trackers in the cargo indicate that it\u2019s being held at <EM4>[Location|Address]</EM4>. We just need someone to go and get it.\n\nThis situation is far from optimal, but I\u2019m hoping you\u2019ll be able to deal with the thieves and return the <EM4>[ItemsToRecover] cargo boxes (all [MaxBoxSize] SCU or smaller)</EM4> to us. I\u2019ve done some quick calculations on the number of reported outlaws and would advise bringing <EM4>additional support</EM4> if possible.\n\nAfter you\u2019ve recovered the cargo, you can bring it to a freight elevator at: <EM4>New Babbage</EM4>. Our logistics team can process it from there.\n\nObviously, the more you can recover the better, but we\u2019ll take whatever you can get.\n\nBest of luck with this one, you\u2019ll need it.\n\n\nAster Remmington\nContractor Liaison Officer\nmicroTech",
